                            <h1>As A Bystander</h1>
                        </div>
                        <div class="block-content mode">
                            <p>Recently, as the Asian American community has faced a spike in hate crimes, it is essential for the entire community to be educated on how to successfully intervene in these circumstances. Again and again, we have seen instances of authorities and citizens ignoring these acts of violence as they occur, turning a blind eye towards the Asian community. Here are some tips on how to safely approach this circumstance:</p>
                            <ol>
                                <li><strong>Distract:</strong> If the situation has not escalated, create a conversation with the victim or even spill a drink. Anything to take the attacker's attention of the victim and for them to realize the victim would be advocated for if attacked in any way.</li>
                                <li><strong>Delegate:</strong> Ask the victim if you can call police authority or seek out help from someone nearby. Try to build support around the victim. </li>
                                <li><strong>Document:</strong> Recording an incident can be very helpful for creating evidence for the victim, and provides firsthand details of the attacker's appearance. However, be sure you are in a safe position to record and be careful not to jeopardize your own safety.</li>
                                <li><strong>Delay:</strong> Try to prevent the attack for as long as possible, even if that means simply standing with the victim, creating distractions, or helping the victim escape. </li>
                                <li><strong>Direct:</strong> Your last option should be directly intervening with your words. Some examples are, "Please Stop", or "That's highly inappropriate" For your safety as well as the victim's, try not to engage in physical aggression. </li>
                            </ol>
                            <p>Follow the five D's and make sure you are safe!</p>
                        </div>
